=Discussion=

[[Tine De Moor]]:

"In Blickle’s view (p. 12) Kommunalismus expresses ‘‘the mutual dependency of independent labor
organizations of burghers and peasants on the one hand, and communes with state functions
on the other (the commune imposed itself as a horizontal principle within the sociopolitical
system from the thirteenth century). These two complementary factors challenged and
altered the wider political regime by means of representation and resistance, establishing
‘communalism’ as a fundamental organizational principle between medieval and modern
times.’’
(https://www.ris.uu.nl/ws/files/20096187/_PUB_SilentRevolution_IRSH_53_Suppl.pdf)

